OL,3,CPrivate school forced to close blames
OL,4,Cfalling numbers and rising fees
OL,6,FAn #18,000 per year Catholic day
OL,7,Fschool in Hampshire has blamed the
OL,8,Fdecline in the number of pupils for
OL,9,Fthe decision to close at the end of
OL,10,Fthe current term.
OL,12,F, which caters for girls and boys from
OL,13,Fnursery to sixth form, said that due
OL,14,Fto a "continued decline in pupil
OL,15,Fnumbers ... the school has now become
OL,16,Funviable".
OL,18,FThere are fears Labour's plans to
OL,19,Fintroduce a 20% VAT levy on private
OL,20,Fschool fees are putting some parents
OL,21,Foff.
